<font color="#FF0000"> THE GRANITE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Mon Feb  1 21:47:13 US/Eastern 1999
</tt><p>
<br>
    A poem from the heart;<br>
              The Granite Wall<br>
          You can see their names carved into stone<br>
          Upon the Granite Wall.<br>
          All taken from us much too soon<br>
          Can you hear their voices call?<br>
          Remember us, please don't forget <br>
          Cry the fathers and brothers and sons,<br>
          The husbands and sweethearts that never returned<br>
          The battles for them are done.<br>
          We lay our tokens of love at the Wall<br>
          As we cry our tears of regret.<br>
          Their silenced voices reach out to us<br>
          And we answer<br>
          &quot;We won't forget.&quot;<br>
                        copyright1985<br>
I will never forget!<br>
          
